# Layout Policy

Use descriptive project directories rather than plugin-branded paths.

- `.agents/`: repo-local agent policy bundle.
- `.planning/`: active human/agent working memory, usually at the workspace root.
- `.workflow-state/`: generated machine/runtime JSON only.
- `.wiki/`: repo-local durable knowledge.
- `docs/adr/`: durable architecture decisions.
- `docs/reference/`: durable runbooks and evidence.

Detected or selected repo type: `{{ repo_type }}`.

Supported repo types: `workspace`, `application`, `library`, `cli`, `plugin`, `data-registry`, and `docs-only`.

Cargo-Inspired Optional Directories:

{% for name in common_optional_dirs -%}
- `{{ name }}/`
{% endfor %}

Use these only when needed. Data registries, docs-only repos, plugin repos, and workspaces may be valid without `src/`. Avoid root `HANDOFF.md`, `docs/plans/`, `docs/brainstorms/`, random workflow-state folders, and `.sinan/`. Child repos keep `docs/adr/`, `docs/reference/`, `.github/`, `.agents/`, `AGENTS.md`, and `CLAUDE.md`; cross-repo planning lives in the parent workspace `.planning/`.
